
itools 0.50.5 (2009/03/27)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.ical             itools.tmx
  itools.csv              itools.isetup           itools.uri
  itools.datatypes        itools.odf              itools.vfs
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.web
  itools.git              itools.relaxng          itools.workflow
  itools.handlers         itools.rest             itools.xapian
  itools.html             itools.rss              itools.xliff
  itools.http             itools.srx              itools.xml
  itools.i18n             itools.stl

A segmentation fault has been fixed in the XML parser, it was trigged
when there was an error parsing a DTD file.  Error messages when parsing
DTD files have been improved too.

In the PDF Markup Language (PML), a file descriptor left open is now
closed, fixing a 'Too many open file descriptors' error.  Handling of
images has been optimized too.

A limit to the length of indexed terms in Xapian has been work-around.

Now non-breaking spaces are preserved when normalizing white-space
characters in text segmentation (itools.srx, bug #336).

Now parsing of tables (itools.csv) and iCalendar files is more correct
(several errors have been fixed) and faster.

The expire date in the 'Set-Cookie' response header (itools.http) is
now correctly encoded.

The 'Context.get_form_value' method (itools.web) has been fixed for the
case when a query parameter has not a value (bug #574).

Now user defined metadata from ODF documents is not extracted for
translation.

The French locale has been updated.


